Major News Items in Leading Japanese Newspapers
TOKYO , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Japanese newspapers Friday .
Asahi , Yomiuri , Mainichi , Nihon Keizai :
-- A Japanese panel announced Thursday standards for screening banks that apply for public funds to boost their capital bases .
A total of 18 major banks and a few regional banks are expected to apply for a total of 2 trillion yen ( about 15.6 billion U.S. dollars ) .
Asahi :
-- The outstanding balance of prefectural government bonds across Japan has exceeded 60 trillion yen ( about 472.4 billion dollars ) .
Yomiuri :
-- The Japanese government and the ruling Liberal Democratic Party decided to add a suspension clause to the fiscal reform law to cope with emergencies .
Nihon Keizai :
-- Japan considers lowering the maximum income tax rates in fiscal 1999 as one way to stimulate the sluggish economy .
